value.value: A hardened plug obstructing the female copulatory opening(s). The copulatory plug is secreted by the male copulatory bulb, although it may have components secreted by the female as well.
A gland discharging secretion through pores in the posterior diverticulum.
A gland discharging secretion through pores on the spermathecal wall.
A generic term for glands discharging their products into female genital elements.
A gland discharging through a pore on the accessory bulb.
The spinning field of the cribellum.
A seta on the cheliceral paturon, densely covered by barbs as in a pipe cleaner, except at the base, which is smooth.
A cheliceral whisker seta arising near the articulation of the fang, bent near its base and accompanying the fang. Escort setae are usually longer than other more mesal whisker setae.
The cup of the anterior median eye.
The cup of the anterior lateral eye.
The shaft of the aciniform gland spigot.
The base of the aciniform gland spigot.
The opening of the gonads located between second and third segment of the opisthosoma. In most of the cases the gonopore is located inside the epigastric furrow.
The silken sac made by the female to retain together the eggs.
The cup of the posterior lateral eye.
The cup of the posterior median eye.
Each of the slit sensillum of the pedicel sensilla stripe.
Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.
The reproductive system of the adult male.
The reproductive system of the adult female.
The male gonad that produces and release sperm.
The tube connected to the distal end of the testis and opens into the proximal part of the unpaired ejaculatory duct.
The unpaired duct connecting the ovaries with the gonopore.
Is the part of the female reproductive system which consists of generative and somatic elements.
The elements of the adult male palp which are involved into sperm transfer.
A spermatheca in the posterior section of the female genitalia. It is connected to the uterus externus or posterior diverticulum by a fertilization duct.
The fertilization duct In the posterior section of the female genitalia, connecting with the uterus externus or posterior diverticulum.

definition.value: In haplogyne condition the fertilization duct acts also as copulatory duct.

value.value: A copulatory duct in the posterior section of the female genitalia.
A cuticular protrusion from the median field of the epigyne.
A gland discharging secretion through pores in a copulatory duct.
A gland discharging secretion through pores in a fertilization duct.
A distinct area (e.g. pore plate) with an accumulation of glandular units.
A short macroseta on the promargin or retromargin of the chelicerae, with blunt tip. Peg teeth occur most commonly in Palpimanoids.
The first of the heart ostia.
The second of the heart ostia.
The third of the heart ostia.
The fourth of the heart ostia.
The fifth of the heart ostia.
A slik structure used to entangle preys.
Organ system responsible for the food uptake and processing.
For Wirkner to do.
The organ system used for gas exchange, lined by cuticle, composed by booklungs and tubular tracheae.
Anatomical system that consists of neurons and its supporting tissues.
Epithelial tube with excretory and osmoregulatory roles connected, to at the junction of the midgut and hindgut.
The median portion of the digestive tube, of mesodermal origin, not lined with cuticle, between the stomach and the stercoral pocket.
A gland of the spinning aparatus, that produces silk.
The organ system responsible for the removal of waste and excess material from the organism.
Organ system which is responsible for silk production and formation.
A large silk gland with elongate lumen and long duct, discharging in a spigot on a anterior lateral spinneret.
A small silk gland with globular lumen and short duct, discharging in a spigot on an anterior lateral spinneret.
